WEBVTT

00:02.070 --> 00:04.338
BRYAN:
No one gives you a handbook
on how to be a parent.

00:04.372 --> 00:08.542
You just arrive home one day
with a tiny, lovable blob

00:08.576 --> 00:09.877
and figure it out on your own.
(whimpering)

00:09.910 --> 00:12.213
Oh, oh, oh.
(gasps)

00:12.246 --> 00:14.882
Oh, who's the baby?
Who's there?

00:14.915 --> 00:17.385
Pets, like our little
Harvey Milkbone,

00:17.418 --> 00:19.887
are training wheels
for raising a baby.
(chew toy squeaking)

00:19.920 --> 00:22.056
They give you a glimpse into
what your life will be like

00:22.090 --> 00:23.057
with an infant.
Oh!

00:23.091 --> 00:25.059
You got him a present.

00:25.093 --> 00:26.427
Like other parents,

00:26.460 --> 00:28.562
we watched our new baby,
riveted

00:28.596 --> 00:30.598
for hours, while he played
in his crib.

00:30.631 --> 00:32.600
(barking)

00:32.633 --> 00:34.602
(whining)

00:34.635 --> 00:36.637
(barking)

00:39.940 --> 00:43.277
We struggled
through sleepless nights.

00:43.311 --> 00:45.313
(Harvey whining)

00:46.414 --> 00:48.082
(angry muttering)

00:48.116 --> 00:51.419
And we nearly exploded with joy

00:51.452 --> 00:53.387
when he uttered
his very first word.

00:53.421 --> 00:54.122
(barks)
(gasps)

00:54.155 --> 00:55.356
Was that "Daddy"?

00:55.389 --> 00:57.091
I heard "Papa."
Oh.

00:57.125 --> 00:59.760
I heard "crazy gay men."
(barks)

00:59.793 --> 01:02.630
And after months
of poop and tears

01:02.663 --> 01:06.134
and countless chewed-up,
hand-cobbled Italian Oxfords,

01:06.167 --> 01:10.771
we achieved the sweetest reward
any parent can ever hope for:

01:10.804 --> 01:12.440
a full night's sleep.

01:12.473 --> 01:14.575
(whining)

01:14.608 --> 01:16.910
BOTH:
Your turn.

01:16.944 --> 01:19.147
(David groans)
Well...

01:19.180 --> 01:21.115
almost a full night's sleep.

01:21.149 --> 01:23.083
Becoming doggy daddies
taught us

01:23.117 --> 01:25.419
how to love something
outside ourselves,

01:25.453 --> 01:28.055
and isn't that what
true parenting is all about?

01:28.088 --> 01:29.623
Okay.

01:29.657 --> 01:31.325
Smelly, how about you,
you want any of this?

01:31.359 --> 01:32.993
(barks)
No? All right.

01:39.500 --> 01:41.469
(knocking)
Ah, come in, Ms. Clemmons.

01:41.502 --> 01:43.137
Just listening
to a sixth grader's

01:43.171 --> 01:46.307
confiscated iPod. That's how
assistant principals stay hip.

01:46.340 --> 01:49.143
(chuckles)
Somebody's gonna learn
how to Dougie.

01:49.177 --> 01:51.279
