Your pooch is fine.
Thank God.

12:17.670 --> 12:20.040
He had excessive air
in his GI tract.

12:20.073 --> 12:22.109
So, gas?
Yup.

12:22.142 --> 12:23.276
We're gonna keep him
overnight,

12:23.310 --> 12:24.311
make sure
the swelling goes down.

12:24.344 --> 12:25.545
He'll be good to go
in the morning.

12:25.578 --> 12:26.613
Thank you.

12:26.646 --> 12:28.615
Mr. Lecompte,
we're ready for your cat.

12:28.648 --> 12:30.650
(yowls)

12:32.786 --> 12:35.222
I can't believe I was going
to let them do that surgery.

12:35.255 --> 12:37.057
Oh, honey, you just wanted
Harvey to be better.

12:37.090 --> 12:38.225
It's okay.

12:38.258 --> 12:40.260
No, it's not okay,
I reacted too fast.

12:40.293 --> 12:42.762
What, what if
that was our son?

12:42.796 --> 12:44.832
David, I could have
just as easily been wrong.

12:44.865 --> 12:46.433
I knew that I wasn't.

12:46.466 --> 12:47.600
(phone chimes)

12:47.634 --> 12:51.071
Oh... oh.

12:51.104 --> 12:52.272
This is Dr. Sawyer.

12:52.305 --> 12:54.774
What?

12:54.808 --> 12:56.409
Oh, my God.

12:56.443 --> 12:57.744
Okay, we'll be
right there.

12:57.777 --> 13:01.248
It's Goldie; she's
in the hospital.

13:01.281 --> 13:03.116
Goldie, Goldie,

13:03.150 --> 13:04.952
are you all right?
BRYAN:
How's the baby?

13:04.985 --> 13:06.086
What did the doctor say?

13:06.119 --> 13:07.787
I don't know,
they're running some tests.

13:07.821 --> 13:09.289
Okay.
Guys, I'm so scared.

13:09.322 --> 13:11.024
I was having cramps and pains.

13:11.058 --> 13:12.625
DAVID:
Okay, let's just wait
to hear what the doctor

13:12.659 --> 13:14.928
has to say, okay? This could be
any number of things.

13:14.962 --> 13:16.429
It's my fault.

13:16.463 --> 13:17.797
Me and Goldie--
we, uh,

13:17.831 --> 13:19.199
we kind of,

13:19.232 --> 13:21.534
you know, we...

13:21.568 --> 13:22.635
We had sex.

13:22.669 --> 13:23.837
And if I broke
your baby,

13:23.871 --> 13:26.206
I promise I'm gonna make
you guys a new one.

13:26.239 --> 13:28.641
GOLDIE:
It's no one's fault,
and Clay's been great.

13:28.675 --> 13:29.776
He's been with me
the whole time.

13:29.809 --> 13:32.112
DOCTOR:
Okay, it's good news.

13:32.145 --> 13:34.514
Looks like it's just a case
of Braxton Hicks.

13:34.547 --> 13:37.350
(sighs)
Unless that is a duet
between Grammy sensation Toni

13:37.384 --> 13:39.219
and fifth season
American Idol winner Taylor,

13:39.252 --> 13:40.287
I am unfamiliar.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.288
DAVID:
It's very normal

13:41.321 --> 13:42.289
in pregnancy,

13:42.322 --> 13:43.523
and although
I'm sure it was

13:43.556 --> 13:44.791
scary for
you, Goldie,

13:44.824 --> 13:47.727
it just means that the uterus
is getting ready to push.

13:47.760 --> 13:48.996
Okay.

13:49.029 --> 13:50.063
But Goldie can't push yet.
The baby

13:50.097 --> 13:51.164
is only 29 weeks--
he's not ready.

13:51.198 --> 13:52.232
Your baby's fine.

13:52.265 --> 13:54.968
Rest of the pregnancy
should be uneventful.

13:55.002 --> 13:56.736
(chuckles)

13:56.769 --> 13:58.571
BRYAN:
I don't know what

13:58.605 --> 14:00.007
I would have done if something
happened to our baby.

14:00.040 --> 14:02.242
That was the scariest moment
of my life,

14:02.275 --> 14:04.377
next to seeing my mom get
out of the bathtub.

14:05.913 --> 14:07.881
(phone buzzing)

14:07.915 --> 14:09.883
What?
Oh, it's the vet.

14:09.917 --> 14:11.584
Oh, get it.
Bryan Collins.

14:11.618 --> 14:14.087
I'm sorry,
what, now?

14:14.121 --> 14:16.323
David.

14:16.356 --> 14:17.390
Yeah.

14:17.424 --> 14:19.526
Harvey Milkbone died.

14:31.871 --> 14:33.873
Harvey.

14:35.242 --> 14:36.709
I just don't
get it, Bry.

14:36.743 --> 14:40.914
He was up, he was walking
around, and then a car hits him?

14:40.948 --> 14:43.283
They take him out for
a walk, he gets loose,

14:43.316 --> 14:44.884
and a car hits him.

14:44.918 --> 14:46.954
It just doesn't--
I-I just can't...

14:46.987 --> 14:48.121
Honey, we can't keep going

14:48.155 --> 14:50.057
over and over this,
trying to make sense of it.

14:50.090 --> 14:53.927
It was just a random,
freakish thing.

14:53.961 --> 14:55.695
(sighs)

14:55.728 --> 14:57.597
I just can't help thinking,

14:57.630 --> 15:00.067
if we'd brought him home
last night, he'd still be here.

15:00.100 --> 15:01.901
Yeah, but we don't know
what would have happened.

15:01.935 --> 15:02.902
Isn't that
the first thing

15:02.936 --> 15:04.304
they teach you
in medical school--

15:04.337 --> 15:06.940
that you can do
all the right things,

15:06.974 --> 15:10.310
but sometimes
patients just die?

15:10.343 --> 15:12.912
Yeah, but it still hurts.

15:12.946 --> 15:14.414
I know.

15:14.447 --> 15:15.448
It's just...

15:16.449 --> 15:19.086
I had this whole picture
in my mind

15:19.119 --> 15:21.254
of me and our boy

15:21.288 --> 15:23.991
playing ball in the park
with Harvey Milkbone.

15:25.858 --> 15:28.161
(voice breaking):
And now our boy's
never gonna know Harvey.

15:28.195 --> 15:30.197
Oh, honey.

15:31.298 --> 15:33.433
This can never
happen to our kid, okay?

15:33.466 --> 15:34.734
I mean it.

15:34.767 --> 15:36.970
I-I just can't go
through that, I can't.

15:39.506 --> 15:41.608
(knocking)

15:41.641 --> 15:43.276
(door opens)

15:43.310 --> 15:44.644
Shania's here with
Goldie and Clay,

15:44.677 --> 15:47.114
and she has something
she wants to say to you.

15:47.147 --> 15:48.548
ROCKY:
Come on.

15:53.020 --> 15:54.187
Hey. How
you feeling?

15:54.221 --> 15:55.955
Much better.
Good.

15:55.989 --> 15:57.424
We told Shania

15:57.457 --> 15:58.758
what happened, and she
wanted to come over

15:58.791 --> 16:00.027
right away to
cheer you guys up.

16:00.060 --> 16:01.828
Oh...

16:03.196 --> 16:04.464
(British accent):
Hello.

16:04.497 --> 16:06.133
I bring the Lord's
thoughts and prayers

16:06.166 --> 16:07.667
to you in this
time of need.

16:07.700 --> 16:09.136
CLAY:
You know,

16:09.169 --> 16:10.537
she almost got kicked
out of school

16:10.570 --> 16:12.505
for dressing up like
this Maggie Smith lady.

16:12.539 --> 16:15.642
But seeing as your dog
got totally creamed,

16:15.675 --> 16:17.510
I made an exception
for you guys.

16:17.544 --> 16:19.179
BRYAN:
Oh, my God,

16:19.212 --> 16:20.647
you're the
Mother Superior

16:20.680 --> 16:22.182
from Sister Act.

16:22.215 --> 16:23.883
Or Sister Act 2:
Back in the Habit.

16:23.916 --> 16:25.685
My dear boys,

16:25.718 --> 16:27.854
loss is never easy.

16:27.887 --> 16:29.522
But have faith.

16:29.556 --> 16:31.324
The light of
the angels shines

16:31.358 --> 16:33.326
brightly upon
Harvey Milkbone.

16:33.360 --> 16:34.227
(laughs)

16:34.261 --> 16:35.395
You shall carry him

16:35.428 --> 16:36.563
in your hearts
forever.

16:36.596 --> 16:38.165
Amen.
Come here.

16:38.198 --> 16:41.068
Oh, thank you.

16:43.236 --> 16:44.837
Oh, hey, Bryan.
Great to see you.

16:44.871 --> 16:46.673
Hi, Father.
Wait, you can see me?

16:46.706 --> 16:48.841
Just the poofy part
of your hair.

16:48.875 --> 16:50.510
Oh.
You should
also know

16:50.543 --> 16:51.678
this confession's being recorded

16:51.711 --> 16:52.879
for quality assurance purposes.

16:52.912 --> 16:54.181
My puppy died.

16:54.214 --> 16:56.349
Oh, boy.

16:56.383 --> 16:57.517
And I know
you're gonna say

16:57.550 --> 16:58.685
he'll always be
in my heart.

16:58.718 --> 17:00.853
But I don't want him
in my heart.

17:00.887 --> 17:02.922
No, you want him in your lap,

17:02.955 --> 17:04.391
licking your face.

17:04.424 --> 17:06.359
What kind of god

17:06.393 --> 17:08.361
lets a nine-month-old
puppy get killed?

17:08.395 --> 17:09.596
Are you mad at God, Bryan?

17:09.629 --> 17:11.531
Hells yes, I'm mad at God.
Well, then,
tell him.

17:11.564 --> 17:12.765
He's a big boy,

17:12.799 --> 17:13.933
he can take it.

17:13.966 --> 17:15.102
Why are you mad?

17:15.135 --> 17:16.703
Well, because he allows

17:16.736 --> 17:18.438
such incredible suffering
in the world.

17:18.471 --> 17:20.373
Look...

17:20.407 --> 17:21.608
I don't want to trivialize

17:21.641 --> 17:23.443
the pain of your dog's death.

17:23.476 --> 17:24.711
But the apostle Paul?

17:24.744 --> 17:27.046
He suffered through
beatings, stonings,

17:27.080 --> 17:28.581
shipwrecks, imprisonments,

17:28.615 --> 17:29.582
homelessness,

17:29.616 --> 17:31.951
and all of that without Wi-Fi.

17:31.984 --> 17:34.421
It sounds like
you're trivializing it.

17:34.454 --> 17:35.755
(sighs)

17:35.788 --> 17:37.790
I'm just saying...

17:37.824 --> 17:39.892
without suffering,

17:39.926 --> 17:42.295
joy and happiness
become commonplace.

17:43.330 --> 17:45.598
Like it or not,
suffering and loss

17:45.632 --> 17:48.235
are what teach us to appreciate
life's blessings.

17:50.403 --> 17:51.738
I'm scared, Father.

17:51.771 --> 17:53.773
(sniffles)

17:55.074 --> 17:56.209
I love Harvey.

17:56.243 --> 17:58.745
I, uh...

17:58.778 --> 18:01.448
I loved him very much.

18:01.481 --> 18:02.749
And losing him hurts.

18:05.485 --> 18:07.854
What if, next, God wanted
to take my baby?

18:11.324 --> 18:12.925
Or David?

18:12.959 --> 18:15.128
Or... Goldie, or Shania,

18:15.162 --> 18:16.929
or anybody that I love?

18:17.964 --> 18:19.332
Wow.

18:19.366 --> 18:21.768
Just listen to the list of
people God has put in your life.

18:21.801 --> 18:24.504
All of them here
to help you

18:24.537 --> 18:26.105
through a time
like this.

18:27.807 --> 18:28.941
Look, Bryan.

18:28.975 --> 18:30.843
The pain that
you're feeling now,

18:30.877 --> 18:32.912
as horrible
as it is,

18:32.945 --> 18:33.946
will eventually

18:33.980 --> 18:36.816
be replaced by moments
of great joy.

18:36.849 --> 18:38.017
Like the arrival

18:38.050 --> 18:40.187
of your baby.
(exhales)

18:40.220 --> 18:41.354
Of course, someday

18:41.388 --> 18:42.489
he, too, will
bring you pain.

18:42.522 --> 18:44.791
Come see me
when he's a teenager,

18:44.824 --> 18:47.126
and knocks up some
professional hula-hooper

18:47.160 --> 18:48.528
he just met at Burning Man.

18:48.561 --> 18:49.696
(laughs)

18:49.729 --> 18:51.831
(sniffles)

18:51.864 --> 18:53.933
So you're saying we can't open
ourselves up to love

18:53.966 --> 18:56.135
without opening ourselves
up to pain?

18:56.169 --> 18:58.171
You got it, kid.

18:58.205 --> 19:00.173
Joy and pain,

19:00.207 --> 19:01.508
sunshine and rain.

19:03.510 --> 19:04.844
I'll miss him, Father.

19:06.379 --> 19:08.615
Do you think we could, uh...

19:08.648 --> 19:10.217
we could say a prayer for him,

19:10.250 --> 19:12.185
wherever he is, that he's okay?

19:12.219 --> 19:13.853
Of course.

19:25.665 --> 19:27.133
(sighs)

19:27.166 --> 19:28.968
Mom, I'll be
in my room

19:29.001 --> 19:31.170
binge-watching Downton
season one.

19:31.204 --> 19:32.705
Okay.

19:34.341 --> 19:35.808
Aren't you, uh...

19:35.842 --> 19:37.009
coming in?

19:38.778 --> 19:40.980
Goldie...

19:41.013 --> 19:42.349
I've been a bad guy.

19:42.382 --> 19:44.217
I lied,

19:44.251 --> 19:46.486
and I cheated,

19:46.519 --> 19:48.187
and... (sighs)

19:48.221 --> 19:49.522
I caused you tons of pain.

19:49.556 --> 19:51.258
But when
I saw you

19:51.291 --> 19:53.593
hurting last night,
it made me realize that

19:53.626 --> 19:57.364
if anything ever
happened to you...

19:57.397 --> 19:58.931
I'd feel like my life was over.

20:00.467 --> 20:02.068
I'm gonna make up

20:02.101 --> 20:04.504
for all the bad things
I did to you.

20:04.537 --> 20:07.474
You don't have to believe me
yet, just watch.

20:16.916 --> 20:19.118
DAVID:
Love isn't always easy.

20:19.151 --> 20:21.254
Sometimes it can really throw
you for a loop.

20:23.155 --> 20:24.957
The minute you start
to love something,

20:24.991 --> 20:27.594
you accept the risk
that someday

20:27.627 --> 20:29.862
it might not be there.

20:29.896 --> 20:32.932
But with the sadness
of lost love,

20:32.965 --> 20:35.535
it's important to treasure
all the wonderful memories

20:35.568 --> 20:37.904
you shared together.

20:37.937 --> 20:39.606
BRYAN:
We had hoped that our puppy

20:39.639 --> 20:40.907
would be like training wheels

20:40.940 --> 20:42.775
for raising a baby,
and he was.

20:42.809 --> 20:46.112
But he also taught us
about love.

20:46.145 --> 20:47.780
How exciting it could be,

20:47.814 --> 20:49.248
and how heartbreaking.

21:00.259 --> 21:01.594
So now, the training wheels

21:01.628 --> 21:04.531
have come off,
and we're still pretty wobbly.

21:10.937 --> 21:12.305
But the truth is,

21:12.339 --> 21:13.906
despite the bumps in the road,

21:13.940 --> 21:15.975
I think we're
a lot more prepared

21:16.008 --> 21:17.744
to handle the ride.

